  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "1. Overview"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The standby domain constitutes the standby RAM, the 8-bit standby controller, the Power Management unit, the Pin Wake-up unit, the Wake-up timer, the VEXT supply monitor, and basic infrastructure components"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The standby domain is supplied by the EVRPR pre-regulator (VDDPD voltage) and is by default clocked by the 70 kHz internal low-power clock source in standby mode"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "2. Topologies"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "There are two possible topologies supported for standby operation depending on the supply connection"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "Standby mode with both VEXT and VEVRSB supplied via common supply rail",
        "Standby mode with only VEVRSB domain supplied and VEXT domain switched off"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "2.1. Standby mode with both VEXT and VEVRSB supplied"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/Aurix%20-%20Standby%20Power%20domain/image2022-8-5_14-47-10.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/Aurix - Standby Power domain/image2022-8-5_14-47-10.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "2.2. Standby mode with only VEVRSB domain supplied"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/Aurix%20-%20Standby%20Power%20domain/image2022-8-5_14-48-14.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/Aurix - Standby Power domain/image2022-8-5_14-48-14.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "3. Topology for our Projects"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "We use the topology 2 where we switch OFF VEXT Supply to achieve sleep current consumption"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "In SCR code, we need to Turn OFF the external supply by making SYS_U33S_SCC_PWR_ON_3V3"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/Aurix%20-%20Standby%20Power%20domain/image2022-8-5_15-1-21.png?api=v2",
